    {
        "header": "3ClinHalluBenchmark",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.14697/2606.14697v1/x2.png",
                "caption": "Figure 2:Overview of theClinHalluconstruction pipeline.ClinHalluintegrates four medical VQA datasets and augments each sample with a structured reasoning trace covering Visual Recognition (V), Knowledge Recall (K), and Reasoning Integration (R). Generated traces are filtered by format validity and answer consistency, yielding validated stage-wise annotations for diagnosing hallucination sources in medical MLLM reasoning.",
                "position": 771
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.14697/2606.14697v1/x3.png",
                "caption": "Figure 3:Evaluation protocol ofClinHallu.Given a medical VQA sample, the evaluated MLLM generates a structured trace and final answer.\nWe then replace selected generated stages with validated reference stages and ask the model to complete the remaining reasoning process.\nThe resulting traces and answers are judged against the references to compute stage-wise hallucination rates (HV\\mathrm{H}^{V},HK\\mathrm{H}^{K},HR\\mathrm{H}^{R}) and answer accuracy (Acc), enabling diagnosis of the main bottleneck in medical MLLM reasoning.",
                "position": 800
            }
        ]
    },
